Fedora CoreOS is created by a team in th: Fedora CoreOS is created by a team in the Fedora Project community called the CoreOS Working Group. It is comprised of official members who have decision-making powers, as well as other contributors. Learn more about this group and how you can get involved on the CoreOS Working Group website.
Join a community of users and contributo: Join a community of users and contributors focused on Fedora CoreOS.

The Fedora CoreOS Working Group sends me: The Fedora CoreOS Working Group sends meeting agendas and minutes and has discussions on their mailing list at coreos{'@'}lists.fedoraproject.org.
